text: Milan Dudić (born November 1, 1979 in Kraljevo, former Yugoslavia, now Serbia) is a former professional football player from Serbia. He is now playing for SK Sturm Graz as defender in the Austrian t-mobile Liga, the highest division in Austrian football. He started playing football with amateur teams and began as a professional player in 1998 with FK Cukaricki. In 2002, he began playing for Red Star Belgrade. He won the Serbian championship two times with the club (2004, 2006) and the cup twice as well (2004, 2006). In 2006, he played with the national team of Serbia and Montenegro at the FIFA World Cup in Germany. All together he played 13 matches for the national team. In 2006, he signed with F.C. Red Bull Salzburg. With Red Bull Salzburg he won the Austrian Championship three times. In 2011, his contract ended and he went to SK Sturm Graz. ==Honours== *Serbian Superliga(2): 2004, 2006 *Serbia and Montenegro Cup (2): 2004, 2006 *Austrian Bundesliga (3): 2007, 2009, 2010 == Other websites == Milan Dudic (Fangemeinschaft FC Red Bull Salzburg) ==Gallery== File:Milan Dudic(1).JPG|Dudić in August 2010 File:Milan Dudic1.JPG|As defender of FC Salzburg File:Milan Dudic5.JPG|Milan Dudic is celebrating his goal File:RBS- Austria Wien7.JPG|Milan Dudic at work vs. FK Austria Wien ==References== Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:Serbian footballers Category:FC Red Bull Salzburg players
